[SN]TITLE[SN]
Paul O'Neill used webcams to direct child rapes in Philippines

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A former teacher has admitted paying men to abuse children as young as three in the Philippines while he directed and watched from elsewhere online.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Paul O'Neill, 57, from Nottinghamshire, preyed on poverty-stricken families, paying Â£6,000 to people who procured children to be abused.
He admitted three counts of rape and a further 27 sexual offences at Nottingham Crown Court.
The CPS said the virtual rape case was thought to be the first of its kind.
He is due to be sentenced later.
